On Sun, Dec 26, 2010 at 4:47 AM, Joe Average <joeaverage(-at-)frontiernet.net> wrote:
> If nothing else works - - - tear the starter down and check the brushes and
 bushings. If they are worn the moving parts of the starter can rub against
 the inside of the starter motor housing and drag... Bushings and brushes are
 cheap and easy to install. Add some fresh grease and new paint and you're
 approaching a rebuilt starter.

Lightly sand the surfaces of the armature a clean the valley between
each contact.

